The paper deals with object recognition and part detection using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new unsupervised method for learning semantic parts, which involves clustering techniques and population encoding. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the internal representations of CNNs, which could fall under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method using datasets and annotations, which could also place it in the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
